commentTextItems.html: full and outside off, and Sanga has a go, but that is too wide

commentPostTextItems.html: Well, that brings us to the end of our coverage for today. Sid Talya has got his report on the game ready in no time. This is Devashish Fuloria signing off. Good night folks.

Mahela Jayawardene: "We were lucky with the toss, but the bowlers stuck to their task. Batting under lights here was going to be tough, but both Kumar and Chandy batted very well and put up a decent partnership. Kumar was disappointed that he missed out in the last two innings, but he made up today. The win gives us an opportunity to experiment in the last game, but we will try to win the game."

Ross Taylor: "Sri Lanka played smart cricket and put us under pressure from the start. We are so close in these games and we are taking positives out from this game. Our bowlers bowled very well. We hope to at least get a win and avoid 4-0."

Jeevan Mendis has been awarded the Man of the Match: "I have been working hard for the last couple of months. I tried my best to get the hat-trick, but I am happy with the three. It is difficult to bowl with the field restrictions, but we are getting used to that."

Sri Lanka finally cross the target after taking an interesting approach in the last five overs as two wickets went down and only 14 runs were scored. In between was Sanga's dismissal of a no-ball, his dismissal of a free-hit ball but finally Sri Lanka come through to take the series 3-0. But the match, pretty much like the entire series, lost its colour due to the two rain interruptions . It started two hours late and New Zealand made slow progress before losing wickets to Jeevan Mendis. That was before the rains came for a second time to reduce the match to a 32-over a side contest.
New Zealand bowlers were unlucky as Sri Lanka's batsman survived against some incisive bowling in helpful conditions to score another comfortable victory.

commentTextItems.html: another solid defensive shot by Sanga, the ball for length on off stump, Sanga got his body behind the ball, and played that with a high elbow, classic.
short of length, solidly defended by Sanga
fuller length, Mathews wanted to drive it through off, but the ball hits the inside half and goes past a diving mid-on for a couple. The scores are finally level.

and a play and a miss now
hits it straight to the mid-on fielder, but it was a free hit, so he is safe again

Boult gets his second, length ball on off and it leaves Sanga's defensive prod, and is taken easily by the keeper. The umpire has asked for a no-ball check, and Sanga is safe. The replays showed that the ball hit the back pad.

commentPostTextItems.html: Sanga was upset with the umpire's decision but came back with a wry smile on his face

commentPreTextItems.html: Sri Lanka are just seven runs short of series win and they don't seem to be in any hurry to get there.

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal b Boult 43 (65b 4x4 0x6 112m) SR: 66.15

dismissalComment.html: round the stumps, length ball, comes in with the angle, Chandimal attempts it to drive it through the covers, leaves a wide enough gap between his bat and pad for an elephant to pass through, the ball hits the top of off. No celebration from the bowler, who could have had him out a few times today.
